SELECT TOP:
  1. The SELECT TOP clause is used to specify the number of records to return.
  2. The SELECT TOP clause is useful on large tables with thousands of records. Returning a large number of records can impact performance.

SYNTAX:

SELECT TOP number|percent column_name(s)
FROM table_name
WHERE condition;

Note: 
  1. We can fetch the No. of data.
  2. We can fetch the Percentage of data.
  
1. Top Number:

    SELECT TOP number ColumnName FROM TableName
    
    SELECT TOP 5 * FROM EMPLOYEE
    
2. Percentage:
 
    SELECT TOPNUMBER PERCENTAGE ColumnName from TableName
    
    SELECT TOP 10 PERCENTAGE * from EMPLOYEE

